getOracleTerritory

public static java.lang.String getOracleTerritory(int from,
                                                  java.lang.String territory)
Return Oracle territory from ISO (ISO territory code). Null is returned for invalid or unavailable territory. Here are some examples. 

         ISO  ORACLE
         --------------------------
         US   AMERICA
         FR   FRANCE
         AE   UNITED ARAB EMIRATES

Parameters:
from - indicating which territory from. 
 TerritoryMapper.ISO
territory - to be converted.

getISOTerritory

public static java.lang.String getISOTerritory(int from,
                                               java.lang.String territory)
Returns ISO territory code from ORACLE (Oracle territory). Null is returned for invalid territory. Here are some examples. 

         ORACLE                ISO
         --------------------------
         AMERICA               US
         FRANCE                FR
         UNITED ARAB EMIRATES  AE

Parameters:
from - indicating which territory from. 
 TerritoryMapper.ORACLE
territory - to be converted.
Returns:
String, ISO territory.
